Hello, this is the error that we are getting:

Screenshot 2025-02-24 1714401486×301 61 KB

We checked all Cancoder IDs, Sparkmax IDs, the wiring is correct, and the CANbus Utilization never reaches past 30%. They are also getting the correct power.

We tried switching to roborio 2 in hopes that will help, but we got the same error.

WE are using swerve drive and Spark Maxes

We are at a loss and appreciate all help and ideas!
If we need to give you more information, please let us know!

Are your CANcoders supposed to be on a CANivore named “canivore”? One of those errors say that “CANbus failed to connect: canivore”, which means we can’t find one that is. If they are on a CANivore, make sure you set its name in Tuner X and use that name in your code. Otherwise, if they’re on the roboRIO CAN bus, pass an empty string (or no string at all).
